2005-12-06  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * misc: another big change to the general API of libmedio. First,
    removed some of the wrongfully placed __MEDIO_PRIVATE__ #ifdef
    which caused third party programs to allocate not enough memory and
    therefore run into certain memory issues. This however required to
    implement another data hiding mechanism to the public classes of
    libmedio such that no unnecessary methods and private methods are
    exposed to the library user. There private classes were created
    which embeed all private members of the main class and are publically
    accessible by it. This also required to introduce default copy 
    constructor and assignment operator methods to all main libmedio 
    classes. Please note that also all copy constructors of header classes
    were modified to NOT copy anything file related like the normally
    corresponding MedIOData pointer. This in fact means that an "="
    operation on two header object 'just' copies their content and
    leave the data pointer intact.
  
2005-12-02  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * testcases/ecat/readwritematrix.cpp: fixed the missing and incorrect
    delete and delete[].
  * CECATFile, CECATDirectoryItem: fixed a bug in the header caching
    routines where it happened that we did a memcpy() over the same
    header, which in fact was not what we wanted to do. Also fixed
    a huge bunch of memory leaks cause by the internals of libmedio.
    Thanks to valgrind for showing the problems.

2005-12-01  Jens Langner <Jens.Langner@light-speed.de>

  * src/include/stubs: implemented include stubs for our public
    header files to hide the version specific differences of the qt3
    and qt4 libmedio versions and allow to have both versions
    installed in parallel. Also adapted the make install target
    to automatically install the stubs in the main include directory.
    Now in public projects, "#include <CMedIO>" instead of
    "#include <CMedIO.h>" must be used.

