    use the save() method without having the header being associated with
    the corresponding CMedIOData object. Now 'false' will be returned
    instead.
  * CMedIOHeader.h: fixed a bug where the missing default assignment
    operator of the base class of all headers caused that also the
    m_pMedIOData pointer was copied, which in fact wasn't the preferred
    behaviour
  * testcases/ecat: modified the ecat testcase to also do some tests
    with the createEmptySubHeader() method.

